Dear All,

Registration is open for the in-person component of the useR! 2025 conference at Duke University, Durham, North Carolina, USA.

The in-person event will take place Friday 8 August to Sunday 10 August, with tutorials, the opening keynote and a networking poster session on the Friday, followed by two days of contributed talks and further keynotes.

Early bird registration is available until 30 April, 2025. Early/Regular/Late registration rates are as follows (in USD)

Student: 150 / 200 / 250
Academia / Non-profit / Government: 350 / 450 / 550
Industry: 500 / 650 / 800

Registration includes two tutorials and the evening poster reception.

For further details, see https://user2025.r-project.org.

Any queries, please contact useR2025 at duke.edu.

A free virtual event will take place on Friday 1 August - save the date! https://user2025.r-project.org/program/virtual/

